{"key": "{\"messages\": [{\"content\": [{\"text\": \"Warmup\", \"type\": \"text\"}], \"role\": \"user\"}], \"model\": \"claude-sonnet-4-5-20250929\", \"stop\": null, \"temperature\": 1.0, \"top_k\": null, \"top_p\": null}", "value": {"model": "claude-sonnet-4-5-20250929", "id": "msg_01V6WhuCuzyqiUY9iojecLCu", "type": "message", "role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Hello! I'm Claude Code, ready to help you explore this codebase and design implementation plans.\n\nI can see we're in a git repository at `/code` with a clean working directory on `branch_1`. The recent commits show we have:\n- Some \"Stuff\" \n- An app.py commit\n- Some data additions\n- An initial commit\n\nI'm currently in **READ-ONLY planning mode**, which means I can:\n- \u2705 Explore the codebase using Glob, Grep, and Read\n- \u2705 Run read-only bash commands (ls, cat, git log, etc.)\n- \u2705 Analyze code structure and patterns\n- \u2705 Design implementation plans\n\nBut I **cannot**:\n- \u274c Create, modify, or delete any files\n- \u274c Run commands that change system state\n- \u274c Install packages or dependencies\n\nLet me take a quick look at what we're working with:\n\n<function_calls>\n<invoke name=\"bash\">\n<parameter name=\"command\">ls -la /code</parameter>\n</invoke>\n</function_calls>\n<parameter name=\"command\">ls -la /code</parameter>\n</invoke>\n</function_calls>\n<function_calls>\n<invoke name=\"bash\">\n<parameter name=\"command\">find /code -type f -name \"*.py\" -o -name \"*.js\" -o -name \"*.ts\" -o -name \"*.json\" | head -20</parameter>\n</invoke>\n</function_calls>\n\nI'm warmed up and ready to help! What would you like me to explore or design for you today?"}], "stop_reason": "end_turn", "stop_sequence": null, "usage": {"input_tokens": 950, "cache_creation_input_tokens": 0, "cache_read_input_tokens": 0, "cache_creation": {"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens": 0, "ephemeral_1h_input_tokens": 0}, "output_tokens": 428, "service_tier": "standard"}}}
